x4freetext: Experiment performed at the High
Intensity gamma-ray Source (HIgS) at Triangle
Universities Nuclear Laboratory, Durham
The target consisted of 11.96 g
of Se powder held in a cylindrical polypropylene
container of density 2.99 g/cm3, with an inner
diameter and height of 1.4 cm and 2.6 cm, respectively.
Scattered gamma rays from the target were
measured by four HPGe detectors, each of 60% relative
efficiency, positioned around the Se target at
degrees, where theta is the polar angle with respect
to the horizontally polarized incoming photon beam
which is defined as the polarization plane, and phi
the azimuthal angle measured from the polarization
plane. A fifth detector, of relative efficiency 25%,
was placed at (theta,phi)=(135,0) deg to distinguish
the spins of positive parity states.
Unknown cross sections
were measured relatively to the known cross sections
measured for the same reaction at Dalinac, Darmstadt
